  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-01-13",
    "date": "2025-04-02T14:26:44Z",
    "text": "Every Drop Counts Act\n\nThis bill expands the Bureau of Reclamation's Small Storage Program, which is a grant program for small surface water or groundwater storage projects in certain western states.\n\nFirst, the bill expands the types of projects that are eligible for grants under the program. Specifically, the bill makes a project eligible for a grant if the project (1) has water storage capacity of recharges no less than 200 acre-feet and no more than 150,000 acre-feet on an average annual basis over the life of the project for storage or use; and (2) increases groundwater aquifer storage, conveys water to or recovers water from groundwater storage, and stabilizes groundwater levels.\n\nNext, it extends Reclamation's authority to carry out the grant program for another five years."
  },
